news.title: Registration of homes in Hyderabad region down 36% in August 2022: Report
news.para: In August 2021, 8,144 housing units were registered in the Hyderabad residential market that includes four districts -- Hyderabad, Medchal-Malkajgiri, Rangareddy and Sangareddy.

news.title: Bengaluru: Of 629 'faulty' buildings, notices issued to owners of 423 to raze structures
news.para: As per a survey, there are 629 ‘faulty’ buildings in the city. The maximum buildings are in south zone (216), followed by west (160), east (101), Yelahanka (84), Mahadevapura (37), Bommanahalli and Dasarahalli (11 each) and nine in RR Nagar.​

news.title: Realty sector in Ernakulam picks up after Covid
news.para: The real estate sector in Ernakulam is showing signs of revival in the post-pandemic period, shows data collected from the registration department.As per the data, registration of documents remains almost the same over the last eight months.

news.title: Lucknow development body seals hotel for violating building norms
news.para: Vice Chairman of LDA Indramani Tripathi told PTI that the SSJ Hotel was sealed on Friday. He said Hotel SSJ International located next to Hotel Virat in Charbagh, was also damaged due to a fire at Hotel Virat in 2018. After which both the hotels were sealed.

news.title: Plan for Noida Metro's Aqua Line extension till Bodaki ready
news.para: As per the DPR, prepared by Delhi Metro Rail Corporation (DMRC), there will be two stations - Junpat and Bodaki - on the 2.6 km-long track.

news.title: Deposit Rs 64 lakh  for us to consider plea against earlier order: Assam REAT to builder
news.para: On June 2 last, RERA (Assam) had directed the builder, M/s Gargi and Associates Private Limited, to return the consideration amount of Rs 34 lakh along with interest to the buyers of a flat for its failure to deliver the flat to them on time.

news.title: Chandigarh: Before 'high price' ends MLA flats dream, a final reminder
news.para: While the UT administration prepares to send a last reminder to Punjab and Haryana demanding release of their share of funds for the project, both states, it is learnt, are not keen to invest in “such a costly project”.

news.title: Lucknow: Fire department surveys 265 buildings
news.para: Continuing its survey for the fourth consecutive day, the fire department on Friday covered 265 establishments in the city, including hotels, commercial buildings, coaching institutes and hospitals.

news.title: Floods may prompt Karnataka government to reconsider Akrama-Sakrama
news.para: Unprecedented flooding and waterlogging in Bengaluru’s IT corridor may prompt the government to rethink plans of pushing the controversial Akrama-Sakrama scheme through. Many civil society members have revived demands to scrap the scheme altogether.

news.title: Highrises along Noida Expressway to get facade lights
news.para: The Noida Authority has changed the building bylaws to make facade lighting mandatory on these buildings. Advent Building, One Sky, Amity University and ATS Tower will get the lights in the first phase.

news.title: Greater Noida authority gives pre-2006 societies two years to get completion papers
news.para: This time extension was approved by the Greater Noida Board at its meeting in Lucknow on Friday, after it was informed that CCs could not be issued to some societies constructed in or before 2016 in Greater Noida due to lapse of time, officials said on Friday.

news.title: Indian Overseas Bank, Bank of Baroda raise MCLR rates by up to 0.10%
news.para: The benchmark 1-year tenor marginal cost of funds based lending rate (MCLR) has been revised to 7.75 per cent against the existing rate of 7.65 per cent.

news.title: Air India Group starts vacating its offices from government-owned properties
news.para: Airline staff in this office as also the ones in Delhi's Safdarjung Complex, GSD Complex and IGI Terminal One will be temporarily located in an office space in Gurugram beginning this month and will move to a newly-built Vatika complex in early 2023.

news.title: CCI dismisses JSW Paints' unfair business practice complaint against Asian Paints
news.para: ​​In an order dated September 8, the anti-trust regulator said no prima facie case of contravention of the provisions of either section 3 or 4 of the Competition Act is made out against Asian Paints.

news.title: Adani Group's open offer for ACC, Ambuja Cements gets mild response from investors
news.para: According to the afternoon updates, only 6.97 lakh shares of Ambuja Cements have been tendered in the escrow Demat account compared to the original offer for 51.63 crore shares from the public shareholders.
